      <span class="headers">PoP: Aid Grimel Quest - Brewing</span>
<p>
<p>
<a name="brewing"><b>Skill Requirement</b></a>: 220 Brewing. Skill modifiers are ignored.
</p> 
<p>
<b>Flag Requirement:</b> Terris Thule. 
</p> 
<p>
Grimel will give you a portable Brew Barrel with 4 slots in it, as well as 3 Fermenting Dusts. <i>Until a recent patch he only provided you with one dust, and you could request more as needed.</i>  
</p> 
<p>
Original text:
</p>
<blockquote> 
<p>
You say, 'I have skill in brewing'
</p>
<p>
Aid Grimel says 'I bet you could make a wicked brew! However I am forced to drink a refreshing drink while out adventuring. I do have this powder that will give the best drinks quite a bite though. Mix the powder in with two Kaladim Constitutionals and a flask of pure water. If you need more dust just ask for it! Put three twice brewed constitutionals and the signet in this drink barrel. As hard as drink barrels are to get these days, you need to return it to me along with the drink you create with it' 
</p>
</blockquote> 
<p>
<i>(Aside: it appears that you can perform normal 4-slot or less brewing combines in this container, but we are unsure if this is intentional, or if it will be patched to change to work only with the quest-only combines)</i>
</p> 
<p>
Turn in the Portable Drink and Portable Brew Barrel to receive the Clay Signet. <b>Do not throw away the Clay Signet!</b> 
</p>
<blockquote> 
<p>
Aid Grimel gulps down a Twice Brewed Kaladim Constitutional and Burps loudly! 'Ahhhh that was refreshing! That should hold me over for quite some time. I see you are quite deft of hand, perhaps you would care to put your jewel craft skills to the test?'
</p>
</blockquote> 
<p>
<b>Item Statistics:</b>
</p>
<blockquote> 
<p>
<b><a href="/items/show_item.php?item=7885&menustr=">Clay Signet</a></b><br />
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <br />
Slot: EAR<br />
